                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. O’Brien states that he has learned indirectly from the prime minister that
                    Japan will decline suggestion of December 18. He adds that a formal reply is
                    being considered, but is not yet ready.</p>
            </div>
